<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#958#0000000019#0000000002#     264.3#0000000003#">Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-264.3:3</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_19.2-264.3_3"/><heading><desig>§ 19.2-264.3:3.</desig><title>Limitations on use of statements or disclosure by defendant during evaluations</title></heading><bodyText><p>No statement or disclosure by the defendant made during a competency evaluation performed pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-169.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-169.1">§ 19.2-169.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#        169.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, an evaluation performed pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-169.5"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-169.5">§ 19.2-169.5<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#        169.5#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> to determine sanity at the time of the offense, treatment provided pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-169.2"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-169.2">§ 19.2-169.2<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#        169.2#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-169.6"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-169.6">§ 19.2-169.6<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#        169.6#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, a mental condition evaluation performed pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-264.3:1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-264.3:1">§ 19.2-264.3:1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#958#0000000019#0000000002#     264.3#0000000001#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or a mental retardation evaluation performed pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-264.3:1.2"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-264.3:1.2">§ 19.2-264.3:1.2<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#680#      19.2#     264.3#0000000001#         2#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, and no evidence derived from any such statements or disclosures may be introduced against the defendant at the sentencing phase of a capital murder trial for the purpose of proving the aggravating circumstances specified in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 19.2-264.4"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-264.4">§ 19.2-264.4.<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000019#     2#        264.4#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> Such statements or disclosures shall be admissible in rebuttal only when relevant to issues in mitigation raised by the defense.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2003 VA CH 1031"><content><span normalizedCite="2003 Va. Ch. 1031">2003, cc. 1031<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2003#001031#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="2003 VA CH 1040"><content><span normalizedCite="2003 Va. Ch. 1040">1040<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2003#001040#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PVD0-004G-K3H4-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 19.2.</desig><title>CRIMINAL PROCEDURE</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 15.</desig><title>TRIAL AND ITS INCIDENTS</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="article"><heading><desig>ARTICLE 4.1.</desig><title>TRIAL OF CAPITAL CASES</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Criminal Law &amp; Procedure</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NEU0RkE1OUQwNUQwNDgxODhEODZCMjkzOTg3NThBNzk7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>Aggravating Circumstances</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6RDg5NUExNUM2RkU3NDUwNUE5NTE5QjZCMzNGNzRBMDU7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6N0RFMEY5RkUxMjlBNEYwRjk3QTM3Q0UyNTI2RjQwOEQ</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>Bifurcated Trials</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NzU1MkY1N0Y1MDJBNDg3NkEyM0VDMjk4Q0FCNTQxQTc7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6N0RFMEY5RkUxMjlBNEYwRjk3QTM3Q0UyNTI2RjQwOEQ</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><classNam